author: Joe Buczek
title: Sports Overtime (October 23, 2015)
text: CENTRAL LAKE – Central Lake improved to 7-2 on the season with a 38-14 non-conference win over visiting Hillman on Friday in our “Overtime on the Road” matchup. (Click here for highlights) The game marked the first meeting between the two teams since 1999. "It's a lot of fun when you have a group of kids come together,” Central Lake coach Rob Heeke said. “We have 12 seniors on a team of 18 and many of them have been playing varsity for three years, so t’s a special group. They deserve it, so we anticipate being competitive in the playoffs and we're going to take it as far as we can go."
